Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Lake treated with acquathol and cutrine on 6/7.  The weather is sunny.
Partly sunny- no rain for last 60 hours
Calm- sunny- heavy rain yesterday afternoon
Bright- strong breeze- temps in 80s for several days
Partly cloudy- warm temps for a week
Cloudy - slight breeze- 3/4" rain on 8/26- cool temps- during previous wk--below 80* (day)- below 60* (night)
Partly cloudy w/ slight breeze- warming temps.
Dark and cloudy with an air temperature of 60 degrees.
Partly cloudy- slight breeze- and 4" of rain on 9/10-9/11.
Partly cloudy with a slight breeze and rain/drizzle.
Sunny with a light breeze and lots of leaves floating in the water.
Calm- bright- sunny- rains last week - lake rose 10".
Bright and sunny with strong breeze.
Bright and windy- rained almost every day in previous week.
Bright and calm- record high temperatures for three days- and the algae bloom is beginning.
Calm and bright.  Part of the lake was treated with Aquathol K and Cutrine on 6/20/87.
Sunny- slight breeze- and 1.5" rain on 7/7/1987.
Bright sunny day- several days of over 90 degrees F heat- and there is algae bloom in the water.
Sunny with slight breeze- heavy algae bloom in progress- lake treated with Cutrine for algae on 8/11/87.
Sunny- slight breeze- 5" of rain on 8/16.
Cloudy and calm- last reading for 1987.
Sunny and breezy- no rain since 5/9/88.
Sunny and clam- no rain for over two weeks.
Sunny and calm- no rain since 5/9/88- weeds are thick- carp are working in bays- lots of boating- fish are biting.
Sunny w/ lt. breeze- no rain for 1 month
Partly cloudy- lt. breeze- 90's- no rain since 5/9- over 100 F yesterday- lake treated w/ aquathol and Cutrine on June 11
Sunny- windy. wind contrib. to poor water clarity
Cloudy with slight breeze- heavy rains in past 3 days
Bright and breezy- lake clearest it has been in 4 years of monitoring
Bright. and breezy- lake treated with aquathol and Cutrine 6/22
Sunny- slight breeze- more weeds this year
Partly cloudy- light breeze- 1.5 in. rain since last reading
Cloudy with drizzle and slight breeze
Sunny- slight breeze- aerator installed in north bay 8/7
Sunny- slight breeze- water in NE bay much clearer- over 6 ft. in weeds
Cloudy- light wind- .25 in. rain early this morning
Cloudy- light wind- 1.1 in. rain 10/16- water quality improving- last report
Sunny- breezy- water discolored from high winds + recent rain runoff
Cloudy- lake treated with diquat + aquathol 6/28- .8" rain night of 6/28
Cloudy- lake treated with diquat- Cutrine 7/24
Partly sunny- slight breeze- .3" rain last night
Partly cloudy- slight. breeze- cool- .75" rain 9/18
Partly cloudy- breeze- rain this morning
Cloudy- 70 F- algae bloom- spraying for weeds
Light breeze- partly cloudy- 87 F- algae has been sprayed.
E wind blowing algae to shore- cloudy- 60 F
Windy- clear- 90 F- lake sprayed 2 days ago
Clear- sunny- 85 F- algae on north shore- swimmers on south beach
Sunny- windy- algae- NE bay weedy- bottom at 5'
Sprayed for algae today- sunny- clear- beautiful day
Windy- muggy- 84 F- heavy boat traffic
Cloudy- heavy duck weed seed and algae- 2.5" rain on 9/11
Sunny- 44 F- algae persisting- N wind at 10mph
Heavy algae- partly cloudy- calm- 38 F
Beautiful- 85 degrees.  Clearest he has seen.
Sunny- weeds developing fast- 3 inches of rain last night.
Sprayed for algae and weeds on 6/8.
Beautiful day.  They sprayed for algae- not much change.
Cool day- the nights have been cool- algal bloom seems low due to cold nights.
Hazy- overcast- not much algal blooms
Sunny day- nice- algal blooms not apparent on the surface
Windy- we drifted a lot- overcast- 50 degrees.
Cloudy day- rained the night before.
1-1/2" rain during past 2 days.  Shoreline repair in progress next to deep hole.
Windy-sunny- low boat traffic-and some fishing boats. Shoreline repair still in progress.
Sunny- low boat traffic. Strong sulfur smell on water at 15' and 21'.  Windy-some clouds. Some pontoon and speed boat traffic. Swim beach open.Shoreline repair finished.
Sunny-low boat traffic-strong sulfur smell on water samples at 15' and 21'
Cloudy and windy-low boat traffic. Strong sulfur smell on dorn sample at 15' and 21'
Water samples at 15' and 21' smelled strongly of sulfur.
Water samples at 15' and 21' smelled strongly of sulfur.
Water samples at 15' and 21' had a strong sulfur smell.
Water samples at 15' and 21' had strong sulfur smell.
Water very murky-low boat traffic.Strong sulfur smell in samples at 21'.
Chunks of grey green globs 1 to 3" diameter floating at or below surface-no sulfur smells in samples
Storms rolling in.  Cool weather.  Strong sulfur smell after 15'
Calm + clear.  Low lake traffic.  Sulfur smell after 15'
Hot all week.  Heavy baot traffic all week. Strong sulfur smell after 15'
Very dry.  Little lake water coming in.  Heavy boat traffic.  Sulfur smell after 15'
Heavy boat traffic all week. Sulfur smell at 15'.

after June storms- the lake level rose over 5 feet- then was drained down to inspect the dams.  Water was restored for July 4th. Today the water level of Park Lake is high with very few shad or carp jumping.  Sunny and 85 degrees.  Water is rushing over the dam and it is hard to find the deep hole.  Water pulled from 15' and deeper has a strong sulfur smell.
High boat traffic in the large area of the lake.  Lily pads and lotus fields are even larger.

High boat traffic the past 2 weeks.  Water level is normal.  Carp jumping in bays.  The location of the deep hole seems to have shifted due to the spring floods.  Strong sulfur smell in water samples at 15 " and deeper.

Partly cloudy and 70 degrees with no rain for 2 weeks.  East winds are blowing duck weed and algae into the lake from the river.  Very low boat traffic.  Strong sulfur smell in water samples at 15 feet and deeper
Partly sunny and 70 degrees.  No boat traffic on the lake.  No rain for 2 weeks.  Carp jumping in bays.
Sunny and 77 degrees.  Very low boat traffic all month.  Schools of small shad in bays.

Sunny and 77 degrees.  Very low boat traffic all month.  Schools of small shad in bays.  Water in the deep hole is brown but in the shallow end of the lake is pea soup green.  There is no sulfur smell in any of the water samples.

Hot weather all last week 90's cooler this week.  Heavy boat traffic on the Memorial day weekend.Shad spawning last week many 8-10 " fish.  Carp spawning now.  Many12-15" fish.  Curly leaf pond weed growing heavy in shallow part of lake east of turtle Island.water is very dirty.
Very windy and hot yesterday.  Heavy rain last night 3+".  Sunny and calm today with 80 degrees.  Low boat traffic.  Schools of shad in the shallows- the carp are jumping.
Sunny and 70's.  No wind. Low boat traffic after labor day.  Shad have moved to the middle of the lake for deeper water.  No rain for 2 weeks.  Fewer lotus this year but more lily pads.
Curly leaf pond weed emerging.  Lily pads are abundant and flowering.  Sunny and breezy in the 80's.  Low boat traffic
Sunny and cool.  Curly leaf pond weed is abundant.  The carp are jumping in the shallows.
Very hot all week.Little to no rain for a while.  Shad fry in shallows.  Very busy boat traffic the last few weeks.  Weeds are dying out.

Temps in the low 70's and partly cloudy.  several fishing boats on the lake today.  It has been very hot and very little rain for the past month.  Heavy recreation traffic on the lake especially on weekends.  Pontoons- jet skis- canoes-kayaks- speedboats- and sailboats.  Lots of lilly pads this year but not as many lotus.
Sunny and 78 with a slight breeze.  Some fishing boats around but low speedboat traffic.  The village is working on the dam by the deep hole.
